 read </span><span class=\"wj\">what David did, when he was in need and was hungry, he and those who were with him:</span> </span><span class=\"v41_2_26\"><sup id=\"Mark.2.26\" class=\"v41_2_26\">26</sup><span class=\"wj\">how he entered the house of God, in the time of</span><span class=\"wj\">Abiathar the high priest, and ate </span><span class=\"wj\">the bread of the Presence, which it is not lawful for any but the priests to eat, and also gave it to those who were with him?\u201d</span> </span><span class=\"v41_2_27\"><sup id=\"Mark.2.27\" class=\"v41_2_27\">27</sup>And he said to them, <span class=\"wj\">\u201cThe Sabbath was made for man, </span><span class=\"wj\">not man for the Sabbath.</span> </span><span class=\"v41_2_28\"><sup id=\"Mark.2.28\" class=\"v41_2_28\">28</sup><span class=\"wj\">So </span><span class=\"wj\">the Son of Man is lord even of the Sabbath.\u201d</span></span></p>\n</div>\n", 
